              <span class="hca-typography--body-2">Flat Button</span>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">A button with no background fill by default. Flat buttons fill with color on press, but do not lift in elevation.</p>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
          <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--mobile">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/buttons/raised-button.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="This is a Raised Button." />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption">
              <span class="hca-typography--body-2">Raised Button</span>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">A rounded corner button with a filled background that lifts and displays an elevation reaction on focus and press.</p>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>

        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
          <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--mobile">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/buttons/floating-action-button.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="This is a Floating Action Button." />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption">
              <span class="hca-typography--body-2">Floating Action Button</span>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">A circular button that lifts and displays an elevation reaction on focus and press.</p>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="app-section">
        <h3 class="hca-typography--title">Choosing a button type</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">When choosing a button type to use in your design, first consider the primary action of your view or component. It is best to make the most primary action stand out visually among all other options.</p>

              <ul>
                <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Some things to think about as you consider what type of button to use:</p>
                <li>
                  <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
                    <h4 class="hca-typography--body-2">Function</h4>
                    <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Is this button the primary action or one of the most primary actions?</p>
                  </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
                    <h4 class="hca-typography--body-2">Dimension</h4>
                    <p class="hca-typography--body-1">When too many elements sit at the same level of elevation, they can lose visual importance. It is best to utilize buttons in a way that highlights the most important actions through elevation. Be conscious of this when choosing between a flat or raised button.</p>
                  </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
                    <h4 class="hca-typography--body-2">Layout</h4>
                    <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Try to use one button type per container in your layout. Utilize different button types in the same container when you need to emphasize one of your actions above the other.</p>
                  </div>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/buttons/button-choice-flat.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Flat buttons are your default button choice." />
              <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption">
                <span class="hca-typography--body-2">Flat Button</span>
                Default button choice</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/buttons/button-choice-raised.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Raised buttons are used for important or primary actions among other less important actions." />
              <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption">
                <span class="hca-typography--body-2">Raised Button</span>
                Important or primary action among other less important actions</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="hca-visual-example">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/buttons/floating-action-button.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="In the event that your entire app or view has one primary action, you can utilize a floating action button to sit above all other options in elevation, thus highlighting it above any other actions." />
              <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption">
                <span class="hca-typography--body-2">Floating Action Button</span>
                Primary action of entire view or app</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="app-section">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-4">
            <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--mobile">
              <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/buttons/button-choice-flat-example.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Default to using a flat button until there is a need for a more important action to highlight." />
              <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption">
