    <article id="section-button-variations" class="app-section">
      <h2 class="app-article-headline hca-typography--headline">Button Variations</h2>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Each of our three button types can utilize different variations based on their role in your design. By default, all buttons are in grayscale.</p>

            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">There are four core variations that can be applied to any button type to help visually distinguish them or add valuable context: primary, success, warning, and danger.</p>

            <p class="hca-typography--support">NOTE: When creating custom variations, you must make sure you <em>at least</em> adhere to a <a href="http://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/" target="_blank">WCAG 2.0 AA accessibility level for visual contrast</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

